title.narrative: Quality standards for ECE are developed, modelled and teacher training system is strengthened

description.narrative: Key results were achieved in early childhood education (ECE) in Tunisia in 2020 with UNICEF support despite the challenges to programme implementation caused by the COVID-19 pandemic, ;including: i) a consolidated roll-out of the new preprimary curriculum, thanks to completion of capacity building for all preprimary inspectors from the 3 responsible ministries nationwide; ii) continued modelling of ECE quality standards;in 3 reference centres, and new involvement of private sector - a key sector player in Tunisia - in this approach; iii) ongoing development of digital solution for the training certification of early childhood educators. | Status:Met | As-of Date:29/12/2020
